The paper proposes a method for image retrieval using deep convolutional features and semantic part-based weighting aggregation. This work is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR), which suggests that cs.CV and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised strategies, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on standard datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
